      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Many of the tools we use every day, such as email clients, word processors, and project management platforms, now have AI features built directly into them, often without any obvious announcement or warning. These features might suggest text, summarise documents, analyse your writing, or even send responses on your behalf, all while processing potentially sensitive information in the background. Because these capabilities are frequently switched on by default, most people are unknowingly sharing data with AI systems as part of their normal working routine. This lesson will help you recognise where AI is quietly embedded in the tools you already use, so you can make more informed decisions about how you work with them. By the end, you will have a clearer picture of the hidden risks involved and some practical steps you can take to stay in control of your information.",
